  "prompt": "How did Stitch Fix start?",
  "response": "Stitch Fix was founded by Katrina Lake in 2011 while she was a student at Harvard Business School. The company began as an online personal styling service that uses data and algorithms to help select clothing and accessories for customers.\n\nLake's idea was to create a personalized shopping experience where customers could receive a \"fix\" or box of clothing items chosen specifically for them by professional stylists, using a combination of personal style preferences and machine learning technology.\n\nThe company started in San Francisco and initially operated with a small team. In 2016, Stitch Fix went public, and Lake became the youngest female CEO to take a company public at that time. The business model involves customers filling out a detailed style profile, receiving a curated box of clothing items, and then keeping and paying for only the pieces they like while returning the rest.\n\nBy combining technology with personal styling, Stitch Fix disrupted traditional retail and online shopping models, offering a more personalized and convenient shopping experience.",
